{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/195", "repo": "rails", "body": "It seems that `:include` option is totally replicate the functionality of `:methods` now. The only difference is nesting that is only available for `:include`. \r\n\r\n\r\nWhy do we need both of them? Can we just add ability of nested attributes for `:methods`(as more natural) and drop `:include`? Because `:include` now looks like a historical feature.", "_id": {"$oid": "52386600bd3543c151012783"}, "issue_id": 195, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1912705", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/195#issuecomment-1912705", "updated_at": "2011-08-26T13:52:20Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan", "login": "bogdan", "gravatar_id": "91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2", "html_url": "https://github.com/bogdan", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F926d19e70f74c20f796d376aafa3c6e2.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 122436, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-08-26T13:52:20Z", "id": 1912705, "owner": "rails"}
